  "prompt": "Why is the period of time for keeping a cellular number not printed on the carrier's fine print either in paper or digital format?",
  "response": "There isn't a universal rule requiring carriers to explicitly print the specific period for keeping a cellular number. The lack of detailed information can be attributed to several factors:\n\n1. Number portability varies by regulatory environment\n2. Technical complexities of number transfer processes\n3. Different policies among carriers\n4. Potential changes in telecommunications regulations\n\nGenerally, number retention policies are available through:\n- Customer service\n- Carrier websites\n- Terms of service documents\n- Contact with carrier representatives\n\nIf you need precise details about number retention, it's best to directly contact your specific cellular carrier.",
